accessibility.text: The Demand for bonds comes from anyone who wants to purchase bonds
The supply of bonds is determined by the need for selling bonds (for funding) and thus does not respond to the price of the bonds
The Supply of bonds comes from the institutions that issue bonds as well as those who previously purchased bonds
The Demand for bonds is low when price of bonds is high and high when the price is low
